Please test with the following patch:

```diff
diff --git a/alacritty_terminal/src/tty/unix.rs b/alacritty_terminal/src/tty/unix.rs
index 0d123b8c..206bb767 100644
--- a/alacritty_terminal/src/tty/unix.rs
+++ b/alacritty_terminal/src/tty/unix.rs
@@ -145,6 +145,7 @@ fn default_shell(pw: &Passwd<'_>) -> Program {
 
 /// Create a new TTY and return a handle to interact with it.
 pub fn new(config: &PtyConfig, size: &SizeInfo, window_id: Option<usize>) -> Result<Pty> {
+    println!("STARTING NEW PTY: {:?}", config);
     let (master, slave) = make_pty(size.to_winsize());
 
     #[cfg(any(target_os = "linux", target_os = "macos"))]
```

Hopefully that should make it obvious if the parameters we start your shell with are incorrect, or if your setup is just broken.

Ok, this is interesting, with this diff:

```
diff --git a/alacritty/src/window_context.rs b/alacritty/src/window_context.rs
index f0b111b5..33b5c624 100644
--- a/alacritty/src/window_context.rs
+++ b/alacritty/src/window_context.rs
@@ -95,6 +95,8 @@ impl WindowContext {
         let pty_config = options
             .map(|o| Cow::Owned(o.into()))
             .unwrap_or(Cow::Borrowed(&config.terminal_config.pty_config));
+        println!("PTY CONFIG: {:?}", config.terminal_config.pty_config);
+        println!("BORROWED PTY CONFIG: {:?}", pty_config);
         let pty = tty::new(&pty_config, &display.size_info, display.window.x11_window_id())?;
```

Original instance:
```
PTY CONFIG: PtyConfig { shell: Some(WithArgs { program: "/bin/zsh", args: ["-l", "-c", "tmux attach || tmux"] }), working_directory: None, hold: false }
BORROWED PTY CONFIG: PtyConfig { shell: Some(WithArgs { program: "/bin/zsh", args: ["-l", "-c", "tmux attach || tmux"] }), working_directory: None, hold: false }
```

new window:
```
PTY CONFIG: PtyConfig { shell: Some(WithArgs { program: "/bin/zsh", args: ["-l", "-c", "tmux attach || tmux"] }), working_directory: None, hold: false }
BORROWED PTY CONFIG: PtyConfig { shell: None, working_directory: Some("/Users/joe"), hold: false }
```

Did a bit more digging. I think I can send a PR to fix the first issue.

For the second issue, I'm in way over my head. I tried the following diff to try to narrow down what's going on:

