The output looks like this:
```
# first CreateNewWindow
FD: 9
PID1: 46656
PID2: 46656
info: core::mem::maybe_uninit::MaybeUninit<alacritty::macos::proc::sys::proc_vnodepathinfo>
info_ptr: 0x16f1052c0
size: 2352
pidinfo_size: 2352

# close the new window and CreateNewWindow again
FD: 16
PID1: -1
PID2: 46857
info: core::mem::maybe_uninit::MaybeUninit<alacritty::macos::proc::sys::proc_vnodepathinfo>
info_ptr: 0x16f1052c0
size: 2352
pidinfo_size: 0
Err: Err(InvalidSize)

# one more time for good  measure
FD: 16
PID1: -1
PID2: 47057
info: core::mem::maybe_uninit::MaybeUninit<alacritty::macos::proc::sys::proc_vnodepathinfo>
info_ptr: 0x16f1052c0
size: 2352
pidinfo_size: 0
Err: Err(InvalidSize)
```

I don't understand why `master_fd()` changes between invocations, but I assume that's the root cause of the rest of the issues.
